casebody.data:
UNITED STATES v. RICHFIELD OIL CO. OF CALIFORNIA et al., two cases. UNITED STATES v. PAN AMERICAN PETROLEUM CO. et al. CHASE NAT. BANK OF CITY OF NEW YORK and Bank of America v. PAN AMERICAN PETROLEUM CO. et al. Nos. 7866-7869. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 14, 1935.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, filed in each of above causes, for dismissal of the causes, with prejudice, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in each of above causes dismissed, with prejudice, and that mandates of this court issue forthwith.
